 <p class="last-updated" class="professional-body">Last updated: February 2026</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">1. Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">CSGA Global is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for all visitors with disabilities. We aim to provide a website that is compliant with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. This Accessibility Statement describes our accessibility initiatives and how users can request assistance.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">2. Accessibility Features</h2>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">2.1 Keyboard Navigation</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">Our website is designed to be fully navigable using keyboard controls alone. All interactive elements can be accessed using the Tab key, Enter key, and other standard keyboard navigation methods. Skip-to-content links are available to bypass repetitive navigation elements.</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">2.2 Screen Reader Support</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">We utilize semantic HTML and ARIA labels to ensure compatibility with screen readers including NVDA, JAWS, and VoiceOver. Images include descriptive alternative text (alt text) to convey meaning to users relying on assistive technology.</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">2.3 Color Contrast and Visual Design</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">Our website meets WCAG AA standards for color contrast ratios, ensuring text is readable for users with low vision or color blindness. We avoid relying solely on color to convey information, using supplementary visual indicators where necessary.</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">2.4 Responsive and Flexible Design</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">The website is designed to be responsive and flexible, adapting seamlessly to different screen sizes and orientations. Users can adjust text size and zoom levels without breaking the layout or losing functionality.</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">2.5 Captions and Transcripts</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">Where video content is provided, we include captions for all spoken dialogue and sound effects. Audio content is accompanied by transcripts whenever possible.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">3. Known Limitations</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">While we strive for full accessibility, some third-party content and external links may not meet our accessibility standards. We are working with our partners to improve accessibility across our ecosystem.</p>
 <p class="professional-body">Some PDF documents on our website may have varying levels of accessibility. We are committed to converting important documents to accessible formats upon request.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">4. Accessibility Standards and Conformance</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">We aim to conform to WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards. Our accessibility efforts include:</p>
 <ul>
 <li>Regular accessibility audits and testing</li>
 <li>Training for our development team on accessible design practices</li>
 <li>Continuous improvement of accessibility features</li>
 <li>Compliance with relevant accessibility laws and regulations</li>
 </ul>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">5. Reporting Accessibility Issues</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or issues, please contact us using the following methods:</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">Contact Information</h3>
 <p class="professional-body"><strong>Email:</strong> accessibility@csga-global.org<br>
 <strong>Phone:</strong> +1 (555) 555-0123<br>
 <strong>Mailing Address:</strong> Accessibility Services, CSGA Global, Level 10, 123 Technology Drive, Sydney, NSW 2000, Australia</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">5.1 Expected Response Time</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">We aim to respond to accessibility inquiries within 5 business days. We will work with you to resolve accessibility issues promptly and may provide alternative accessible formats of content if needed.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">6. Accessibility Features for Specific Needs</h2>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">6.1 Dyslexia Support</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">We use clear, sans-serif fonts and appropriate line spacing to support readers with dyslexia. We recommend users with dyslexia consider using specialized reading software in conjunction with our website.</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">6.2 Motor Accessibility</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">Our website supports voice control and keyboard navigation for users with motor disabilities. All interactive elements are appropriately sized to be easily clickable.</p>
 <h3 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">6.3 Cognitive Accessibility</h3>
 <p class="professional-body">We use clear language, logical structure, and consistent navigation to support users with cognitive disabilities. We provide explanations for technical terms and avoid unnecessary jargon where possible.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">7. Third-Party Content and External Links</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">While we strive to ensure all linked external websites are accessible, we cannot guarantee the accessibility of third-party content. If you encounter accessibility issues with linked content, please contact us and we will do our best to assist you.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">8. Accessibility Statement Updates</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">We regularly review and update this Accessibility Statement to reflect improvements and changes to our website. Last updated: February 2026.</p>
 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">9. Legal Framework</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">This Accessibility Statement reflects our commitment to compliance with applicable accessibility legislation, including the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), the Web Accessibility Directive, and similar regulations in other jurisdictions.</p>
